## Docker Notes ##

Docker Basics Commands

1. Docker Pull <Image Name>                                     <Pulles image from Docker Hub>
2. Docker Run <Image Name>                                      <To run the container with pulling Image>
3. Docker ps                                                    <To check which container are running>
4. Docker ps -a                                                 <To check all running container>
5. Docker rm <Image Id or Name>                                 <To delete the container>
6. Docker rmi <Image Id or Name>                                <To delete the image> 
7. Docker stop <Image Id or Name>                               <To stop running container>
8. Docker start <Image Id or Name>                              <To start stoped container>
9. Docker Logs <Image Id or Name>                               <To check all logs of container>
10.Docker exec <Image Id or Name> /bin/bash                     <To login to intractive mode of container>